Founded in 1820, Worcester is the "capital of the Breede River Valley".
This area includes Ceres, Tulbagh, Montagu, Robertson and Ashton, all known for fruit and wine production.
Mission stations in this area provided a haven for freed slaves, labourers and the dispossessed Khoekhoen.
